Cape Town is known as the Mother City but this weekend it became the Rebel City as it celebrated all things powered by pistons. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cape Town is known as the Mother City, but this past weekend it became the Rebel City as it celebrated all things powered by pistons. The first Festival of Rebels, which showcases everything motor-bikes and biking, was hosted in Cape Town. READ: Motorist filmed driving over 300km/h on Joburg highway “This is a very premium motorcycle festival. It is a Harley Davidson lifestyle festival. It's everything Harley-Davidson inspired,” said festival organiser Ryan Moir. Many were attracted to the virtual reality experience and for those who never thought of riding a bike, the experts were right there to lend you a helping hand.